The results are presented in two phases: before and after the World Health Organization (WHO) travel advisory since this was a major event in SARS-struck Toronto. Not only did it have an impact on the willingness of both domestic and international visitors to travel to Toronto, it came as a great surprise, and was widely regarded as an inappropriate, even ridiculous international response, particularly as it came at a time when the number of incidences of SARS was in decline and no new cases had been reported for a week. From the first incidence of SARS in Toronto, there were substantial price cuts and layoffs in an industry that was already ailing. They can be viewed as being part of a recovery strategy and as attempts to make establishments more competitive. They are not reported in detail here although they were widely reported in the media and these reports added to the malaise. 


